album.title: The Complete Ella Fitzgerald Song Books

track.name: A Foggy Day
comments: Ella used to impersonate Louie all the time.  My favorite singer of all time got the privilege of  seeing her in concert twice, shortly before she died. She was legally blind and had to sit down a lot at the last concert.  The women still had major chops!
Ella sounds surprisingly like Louis Armstrong,
nothing british in the british museum btw.  It only displays stuff the british nicked from all over the world
awful, he just cuts through the emotion of the song. Where is the version that Ella sung................ :(
yes, and why isn't it listed as a duet with Louis?
What a wonderfull song, such a marvelous voices
